<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Juventus have signed Spain striker Alvaro Morata on a season-long loan from Atletico Madrid for Â£9m, the Italian champions announced on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The agreement also gives Juve an option to buy the 27-year-old at the end of the season for Â£41m to be paid over three years.</p>

<p>They could otherwise take him on loan again for the 2021-22 season for another Â£9m and then buy him outright in 2022 at a reduced cost of Â£32m.</p>

